WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.360
Do please take your Bibles and turn with me to John chapter 8.

2
00:00:08.360 --> 00:00:12.560
We're going to be reading a few verses from there and a bit later on we'll look at John

3
00:00:12.560 --> 00:00:13.560
chapter 20.

4
00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:17.960
It's also in your worship guides if you want to look there.

5
00:00:17.960 --> 00:00:21.120
Just as you're turning, let me just say over the next few weeks as we're leading

6
00:00:21.120 --> 00:00:26.960
up to Easter, like many other churches, we will be focusing our attention on Jesus.

7
00:00:27.720 --> 00:00:32.760
We're going to do so particularly by looking at the I am statements of Jesus in the

8
00:00:32.760 --> 00:00:34.880
Gospel of John.

9
00:00:34.880 --> 00:00:38.760
There are seven of them and each of them are connected to a picture.

10
00:00:38.760 --> 00:00:42.640
You have Jesus in John 6 saying I am the bread of life.

11
00:00:42.640 --> 00:00:46.440
You have him in John 8 saying I am the light of the world.

12
00:00:46.440 --> 00:00:48.920
And then chapter 10, I am the good shepherd.

13
00:00:48.920 --> 00:00:50.760
I am the door.

14
00:00:50.760 --> 00:00:53.520
In chapter 11 he says I am the resurrection and the life.

15
00:00:53.520 --> 00:00:56.080
Chapter 14, I am the way, the truth and the life.

16
00:00:56.080 --> 00:01:00.840
And then finally in chapter 15, I am the true vine.

17
00:01:00.840 --> 00:01:05.320
But then there are other times when he simply says I am.

18
00:01:05.320 --> 00:01:08.720
So when you're looking at all of that happening in John, you see that the thing that all of

19
00:01:08.720 --> 00:01:12.000
those statements have in common are those two words, I am.

20
00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:15.000
And then there are other times in the book where there's no picture connected to it,

21
00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:17.320
but Jesus says I am.

22
00:01:17.320 --> 00:01:18.840
So what is he talking about?

23
00:01:18.840 --> 00:01:25.480
Well, let's read John chapter 8 beginning in verse 31 together.

24
00:01:25.480 --> 00:01:31.640
So Jesus said to the Jews who had believed him, if you abide in my word, you are truly

25
00:01:31.640 --> 00:01:36.960
my disciples and you will know the truth and the truth will set you free.

26
00:01:36.960 --> 00:01:43.160
They answered him, we are offspring of Abraham and have never been enslaved to anyone.

27
00:01:43.160 --> 00:01:46.160
How is it that you say you will become free?

28
00:01:46.160 --> 00:01:48.280
Jesus answered them.

29
00:01:48.280 --> 00:01:54.200
Truly truly I say to you, everyone who practices sin is a slave to sin.

30
00:01:54.200 --> 00:01:57.080
A slave does not remain in the house forever.

31
00:01:57.080 --> 00:01:58.960
The son remains forever.

32
00:01:58.960 --> 00:02:03.280
So if the son sets you free, you will be free indeed.

33
00:02:03.280 --> 00:02:06.440
Then go to verse 51.

34
00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:11.720
Truly truly I say to you, if anyone keeps my word, he will never see death.

35
00:02:11.720 --> 00:02:15.480
The Jews said to him, now we know that you have a demon.

36
00:02:15.480 --> 00:02:17.800
Abraham died as did the prophets.

37
00:02:17.800 --> 00:02:23.040
Prophets, yet you say, if anyone keeps my word, he will never taste death.

38
00:02:23.040 --> 00:02:28.840
Are you greater than our father Abraham, who died and the prophets died?

39
00:02:28.840 --> 00:02:32.080
Who do you make yourself out to be?

40
00:02:32.080 --> 00:02:37.720
Jesus answered, if I glorify myself, my glory is nothing.

41
00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:43.360
It is my father who glorifies me of whom you say he is our God.

42
00:02:43.360 --> 00:02:45.200
But you have not known him.

43
00:02:45.200 --> 00:02:46.800
I know him.

44
00:02:46.800 --> 00:02:51.360
If I were to say that I do not know him, I would be a liar like you, but I do know

45
00:02:51.440 --> 00:02:53.640
him and I keep his word.

46
00:02:53.640 --> 00:02:58.240
Your father Abraham rejoiced that he would see my day.

47
00:02:58.240 --> 00:03:01.160
He saw it and was glad.

48
00:03:01.160 --> 00:03:07.080
So the Jews said to him, you are not yet 50 years old and have you seen Abraham?

49
00:03:07.080 --> 00:03:15.600
Jesus said to them, truly, truly, I say to you, before Abraham was, I am.

50
00:03:15.600 --> 00:03:18.200
So they picked up stones to throw at him.

51
00:03:18.240 --> 00:03:22.400
But Jesus hit himself and went out of the temple.

52
00:03:22.400 --> 00:03:25.320
This is the word of the Lord.

53
00:03:25.320 --> 00:03:28.320
Let's pray.

54
00:03:28.320 --> 00:03:34.000
Lord, as we've just heard from the very words of Jesus, that your word is truth.

55
00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:37.520
And your truth sets us free.

56
00:03:37.520 --> 00:03:42.760
Lord, I pray that you would speak to us now through the truth of your word.

57
00:03:42.760 --> 00:03:47.320
Lord, I pray that we would receive it by faith and that we would know the life

58
00:03:47.360 --> 00:03:50.880
and the freedom that is found in Jesus.

59
00:03:50.880 --> 00:03:53.160
We ask all of this in his name.

60
00:03:53.160 --> 00:03:54.160
Amen.

61
00:03:55.320 --> 00:03:59.880
All right, so we're looking together now at the gospel of John.

62
00:03:59.880 --> 00:04:04.160
And it might be helpful for just to start off by saying, well, what is a gospel?

63
00:04:04.160 --> 00:04:06.040
That we talk about that from time to time.

64
00:04:06.040 --> 00:04:07.520
What what are the gospels?

65
00:04:07.520 --> 00:04:11.280
Well, the gospels are these biographical accounts of Jesus.

66
00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:15.960
And John is one of four biographical accounts that are in the New Testament.

67
00:04:15.960 --> 00:04:19.520
You can look at other letters that are written as kind of eyewitness testimony,

68
00:04:19.520 --> 00:04:24.200
but you have these in particular that are kind of put for us as biographies.

69
00:04:24.720 --> 00:04:30.520
And so what is writing here about Jesus isn't putting him before us as mere legend,

70
00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:33.720
but as history.

71
00:04:33.720 --> 00:04:38.840
And what is being written is being written as an eyewitness account.

72
00:04:39.560 --> 00:04:43.240
And it's being written within the lifetime of the eyewitnesses.

73
00:04:43.240 --> 00:04:47.960
And John is putting himself forward as one of these eyewitnesses of Jesus.

74
00:04:48.280 --> 00:04:53.880
And so we might naturally wonder, well, how can we know that this is an eyewitness account?

75
00:04:53.880 --> 00:04:56.320
How can we know that it's genuine?

76
00:04:56.320 --> 00:04:59.040
Well, could I just make a book recommendation before we move on?

77
00:04:59.040 --> 00:05:03.480
I'm just going to briefly touch on this, but look at Can I Trust the Gospels

78
00:05:03.480 --> 00:05:06.920
by New Testament scholar Peter Williams?

79
00:05:07.320 --> 00:05:10.640
But there are several different lines of evidence in that book that he looks at.

80
00:05:10.640 --> 00:05:13.560
But one of the things that he draws your attention to in the book

81
00:05:13.560 --> 00:05:18.080
is how the Gospels are just dripping with all kinds of details.

82
00:05:19.560 --> 00:05:22.920
And the level of seemingly insignificant details,

83
00:05:22.920 --> 00:05:25.840
he kind of makes the case that they actually attest to the fact

84
00:05:25.840 --> 00:05:30.120
that they were written by people who were extremely familiar with the context

85
00:05:30.680 --> 00:05:32.640
they were writing about.

86
00:05:32.640 --> 00:05:34.880
One of the things I find interesting that he talks about

87
00:05:34.880 --> 00:05:38.440
are the are the different names that are scattered throughout the Gospels.

88
00:05:38.840 --> 00:05:41.520
You read about the names of specific places, right?

89
00:05:41.520 --> 00:05:46.000
So the Gospel writers are writing about the names of towns and regions

90
00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:48.200
and bodies of water and botany.

91
00:05:48.360 --> 00:05:53.600
And all of it lines up with what we know about that particular place,

92
00:05:53.600 --> 00:05:55.960
at that particular time.

93
00:05:55.960 --> 00:06:00.160
Now, that cannot be said for other Gospels that were written much later on.

94
00:06:00.160 --> 00:06:03.360
Like you can look at other other Gospels, the Gospel of Thomas or Barnabas

95
00:06:03.360 --> 00:06:07.080
or whatever that were written who do not have that level of specificity

96
00:06:07.080 --> 00:06:10.400
when it comes to these names and places.

97
00:06:10.400 --> 00:06:14.360
And so it's showing that they were not written within that kind of eyewitness

98
00:06:14.720 --> 00:06:18.000
timeframe or rather kind of forgeries later on.

99
00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:20.520
You also get the names of people.

100
00:06:20.520 --> 00:06:24.400
And so these names of people, they line up with the names of people at the time,

101
00:06:24.400 --> 00:06:27.520
of course, but also these names of people are there

102
00:06:28.080 --> 00:06:33.080
because they could also attest to the fact that these were eyewitness accounts.

103
00:06:33.080 --> 00:06:35.880
So there's some people that are named and other people that are not named.

104
00:06:35.880 --> 00:06:38.760
And generally speaking, it's believed that the people that are named are named

105
00:06:38.760 --> 00:06:42.680
because as these letters are first being circulated, as these biographical accounts

106
00:06:42.680 --> 00:06:47.040
are being circulated, these people are still living and they can talk about

107
00:06:47.040 --> 00:06:47.840
what they have seen.

108
00:06:47.840 --> 00:06:51.400
You can go and speak to any number of them.

109
00:06:52.400 --> 00:06:56.640
But the most extraordinary claim in the Gospel is another name.

110
00:06:56.640 --> 00:06:59.480
It's the name that Jesus ascribes to himself.

111
00:07:01.160 --> 00:07:04.560
And by the way, if the Gospels were just making ordinary claims,

112
00:07:04.560 --> 00:07:06.360
they would be taken as history.

113
00:07:06.360 --> 00:07:11.120
You can read about the Emperor Tiberius and his four accounts of his life

114
00:07:11.120 --> 00:07:13.120
and so much other history at the time.

115
00:07:13.240 --> 00:07:14.560
So they would be taking as history.

116
00:07:14.560 --> 00:07:19.080
But the reason why there is doubt cast upon them is not because they can't be

117
00:07:19.080 --> 00:07:22.880
backed up historically, but rather because of the extraordinary claims

118
00:07:22.880 --> 00:07:27.640
that they make, particularly about who Jesus is and what he did.

119
00:07:28.720 --> 00:07:32.160
And all of that's kind of summed up in this name that Jesus ascribes to himself.

120
00:07:33.160 --> 00:07:37.040
Well, we've just read this account in John chapter eight, where Jesus is speaking

121
00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:41.720
to a group of Jews and he's teaching them that he came to bring the truth

122
00:07:41.720 --> 00:07:43.680
and the truth that he brings would set people free.

123
00:07:43.680 --> 00:07:45.480
They are offended by this.

124
00:07:46.760 --> 00:07:48.160
And so what do you mean set free?

125
00:07:48.160 --> 00:07:52.000
We're not enslaved to anything or any body, but the reality is

126
00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:55.920
they like everyone are enslaved to sin and to death.

127
00:07:55.920 --> 00:07:58.160
And that's what he has come to set us free from.

128
00:07:58.560 --> 00:08:01.400
But they thought they were OK because they were children of Abraham.

129
00:08:01.400 --> 00:08:04.680
They thought they were OK because of their ethnicity, in other words.

130
00:08:05.280 --> 00:08:08.640
So they were thinking, well, who does this guy think he is?

131
00:08:09.040 --> 00:08:12.080
And then Jesus makes that stunning claim in verse 58.

132
00:08:12.520 --> 00:08:16.800
Truly, truly, I say to you before Abraham was I am.

133
00:08:18.240 --> 00:08:21.720
Essentially, he doesn't say before Abraham was I was like that would be

134
00:08:21.720 --> 00:08:25.440
quite an extraordinary claim to say he was somehow made an appearance back then.

135
00:08:25.720 --> 00:08:28.720
But he's claiming something far greater than that.

136
00:08:29.280 --> 00:08:32.360
And you can see that the people are so enraged that they're picking up

137
00:08:32.360 --> 00:08:36.880
these stones to stone him because of this claim, because they knew what he was

138
00:08:36.880 --> 00:08:41.480
claiming by ascribing this name, I am to himself.

139
00:08:42.800 --> 00:08:44.560
So what we're going to do for the next few moments.

140
00:08:44.560 --> 00:08:48.320
And then as we really look through the the Gospel of John as a whole

141
00:08:48.320 --> 00:08:51.920
for the next few weeks, we're going to be asking these questions.

142
00:08:52.520 --> 00:08:54.560
First of all, who is Jesus?

143
00:08:54.560 --> 00:08:57.400
What is this name all about?

144
00:08:57.440 --> 00:08:59.440
Also, what did Jesus do?

145
00:08:59.440 --> 00:09:02.560
And lastly, how we should respond to him.

146
00:09:03.480 --> 00:09:05.960
OK, so what does John tell us about this this name?

147
00:09:05.960 --> 00:09:06.760
Who is Jesus?

148
00:09:06.760 --> 00:09:09.840
What is this name that he ascribes to himself?

149
00:09:10.240 --> 00:09:13.000
Well, let's turn together to John chapter 20.

150
00:09:13.920 --> 00:09:18.760
John chapter 20, we're going to look at verses 30 and 31.

151
00:09:20.480 --> 00:09:24.520
So while John is writing history, he's not intending this to be like

152
00:09:24.520 --> 00:09:28.720
like a photograph where you've got every just kind of detail there in the moment.

153
00:09:29.040 --> 00:09:32.320
It's more like a painting that he is painting.

154
00:09:32.320 --> 00:09:37.560
So what he is saying is factual, but yet he is not just presenting the facts.

155
00:09:37.560 --> 00:09:40.240
He is preaching a sermon, so to speak.

156
00:09:40.960 --> 00:09:44.120
He's he's he's he's he's crafting what he is writing.

157
00:09:44.120 --> 00:09:46.480
And he's right up front about this.

158
00:09:46.480 --> 00:09:51.040
So let's read John 20 verses 30 and 31 says, Now, Jesus did many other

159
00:09:51.080 --> 00:09:56.400
signs in the presence of the disciples, which are not written in this book.

160
00:09:57.480 --> 00:10:01.400
But these are written so that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ,

161
00:10:01.840 --> 00:10:08.080
the Son of God, and that by believing you may have life in his name.

162
00:10:09.160 --> 00:10:12.840
So he writes about what Jesus did, but he's not merely writing about

163
00:10:12.840 --> 00:10:15.120
something about someone who was.

164
00:10:15.120 --> 00:10:20.400
He says, I'm writing so that you might know who Jesus is, that he is the Christ.

165
00:10:21.080 --> 00:10:25.320
So he's writing that we might know the Jesus that he came to know.

166
00:10:26.120 --> 00:10:32.320
And he tells us that we too can have life by believing in his name.

167
00:10:33.280 --> 00:10:34.680
OK, so his name is mentioned here.

168
00:10:34.680 --> 00:10:37.560
So what is this name?

169
00:10:37.560 --> 00:10:40.800
Well, when scripture speaks about names, it's speaking about more than

170
00:10:41.160 --> 00:10:45.080
just just a label that somebody has on himself.

171
00:10:45.080 --> 00:10:46.880
Well, I think you can get this in other cultures.

172
00:10:47.880 --> 00:10:52.560
I know I haven't talked to him for a long time, but he was from Ghana.

173
00:10:52.920 --> 00:10:54.480
And his name is Kofi.

174
00:10:54.720 --> 00:10:57.800
And his name is Kofi because he was born on a Friday.

175
00:10:57.800 --> 00:11:01.280
Right. So there's a lot of people in cultures there where their name is

176
00:11:01.280 --> 00:11:03.080
attached to the day of the week they were born.

177
00:11:03.080 --> 00:11:05.360
So their name tells you something about themselves.

178
00:11:05.600 --> 00:11:08.600
And there are certain like Native American cultures where people's

179
00:11:08.600 --> 00:11:12.960
names can change over time to connect more with their personality

180
00:11:12.960 --> 00:11:17.000
or their or their accomplishments or major events in their life.

181
00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:20.680
So their name reveals something about them.

182
00:11:21.200 --> 00:11:22.760
And that's what's going on in scripture.

183
00:11:22.760 --> 00:11:27.280
When God's name is given, he is revealing something about who he is.

184
00:11:27.280 --> 00:11:29.760
It's a revelation of his nature.

185
00:11:30.520 --> 00:11:32.440
So you get this next chapter three.

186
00:11:34.520 --> 00:11:38.880
You get this account of God making himself known to Moses in the burning bush,

187
00:11:38.880 --> 00:11:42.240
this bush that is burning, but not consumed.

188
00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:46.920
And at the burning bush, God speaks to Moses and he tells him about how he's going

189
00:11:46.920 --> 00:11:51.360
to deliver his people from slavery and how he's going to bring them into

190
00:11:51.360 --> 00:11:52.920
the land that he had promised them.

191
00:11:52.920 --> 00:11:57.520
And then Moses then asks this important question next to this three, 13 and 14.

192
00:11:58.280 --> 00:12:01.600
He says, if I come to the people of Israel and say to them,

193
00:12:01.840 --> 00:12:06.840
the God of your fathers has sent me to you and they ask me, what is his name?

194
00:12:07.920 --> 00:12:10.240
What shall I say to them?

195
00:12:10.240 --> 00:12:16.160
God said to me, yes, God said to Moses, I am who I am.

196
00:12:16.800 --> 00:12:19.120
Say this to the people of Israel.

197
00:12:19.120 --> 00:12:23.040
I am has sent me to you.

198
00:12:23.760 --> 00:12:26.160
So Moses, this is my name.

199
00:12:26.160 --> 00:12:28.720
I am who I am.

200
00:12:28.720 --> 00:12:31.600
So his name is revealing that God absolutely is.

201
00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:34.520
So what is this name telling us about God?

202
00:12:34.520 --> 00:12:36.600
What does he mean when he says I am?

203
00:12:37.240 --> 00:12:39.960
Well, there's a whole lot that we could list out.

204
00:12:40.520 --> 00:12:41.880
So just take a couple.

205
00:12:41.880 --> 00:12:45.560
One of the things he's telling us about himself is that he is eternal.

206
00:12:45.560 --> 00:12:48.000
Unlike us, he doesn't have a beginning.

207
00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:49.280
He doesn't have an ending.

208
00:12:49.280 --> 00:12:51.160
He simply is.

209
00:12:52.600 --> 00:12:55.720
He's eternal from everlasting to everlasting.

210
00:12:55.720 --> 00:12:57.200
He is God.

211
00:12:57.200 --> 00:13:00.240
But also he's telling us that he is self-existent.

212
00:13:01.120 --> 00:13:04.640
OK, so the bush there is an image that's there for us.

213
00:13:04.640 --> 00:13:09.560
So he is the bush is burning, but is not consumed as he announces

214
00:13:09.600 --> 00:13:11.280
that he is who he is.

215
00:13:11.800 --> 00:13:14.160
So like unlike any other fire,

216
00:13:15.360 --> 00:13:17.840
this fire does not need fuel.

217
00:13:18.320 --> 00:13:22.440
So when God is speaking through this burning bush and he's saying I am,

218
00:13:22.440 --> 00:13:29.320
he's also saying that his existence is not contingent upon anything outside of himself.

219
00:13:30.120 --> 00:13:34.760
Instead, all reality is contingent upon him.

220
00:13:35.520 --> 00:13:39.240
Right before anything was he didn't need anything to exist.

221
00:13:40.120 --> 00:13:46.320
And he then brings everything into being and he's in no way dependent upon his creation.

222
00:13:46.320 --> 00:13:47.800
He simply is.

223
00:13:47.800 --> 00:13:52.840
So he's the creator, the sustainer, and he's well able to be the savior of his people.

224
00:13:53.040 --> 00:13:57.360
And this name, the I am, which means to be, goes on.

225
00:13:58.040 --> 00:14:05.960
I, yeah, it goes on to be the kind of root of the name that is God's name most used for

226
00:14:06.720 --> 00:14:08.360
or in the Old Testament.

227
00:14:08.360 --> 00:14:12.360
So his name is Yahweh right throughout the Old Testament or Lord.

228
00:14:12.440 --> 00:14:18.640
And at the root of that is to be this Yah Yahweh, I am who I am.

229
00:14:20.200 --> 00:14:22.640
Now back to the Gospel of John.

230
00:14:22.640 --> 00:14:27.840
This is the very name that Jesus is taking upon himself.

231
00:14:28.480 --> 00:14:33.000
You can see why people reacted with such hostility towards him.

232
00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:36.520
They know that he's claiming to be the I am who I am.

233
00:14:36.520 --> 00:14:38.760
How could this possibly be?

234
00:14:38.760 --> 00:14:43.440
He's claiming to be God himself manifest in the flesh.

235
00:14:44.440 --> 00:14:47.040
You see this not just in that statement and the I am statements.

236
