In fact, he uses that word 98 times in this gospel.

470
00:30:34.180 --> 00:30:37.080
So this is not hidden in any way.

471
00:30:37.280 --> 00:30:38.480
So it's really important.

472
00:30:38.480 --> 00:30:41.080
So what does it mean to believe in Jesus?

473
00:30:42.080 --> 00:30:45.080
What's more than just intellectual ascent?

474
00:30:45.080 --> 00:30:46.580
Like do you believe this fact?

475
00:30:46.580 --> 00:30:47.380
Do you believe this fact?

476
00:30:47.380 --> 00:30:48.280
Do you believe this fact?

477
00:30:48.280 --> 00:30:49.080
Repeat after me.

478
00:30:49.080 --> 00:30:53.080
You know, it is a complete trust in Jesus.

479
00:30:53.080 --> 00:30:55.680
It's in trusting ourselves to him.

480
00:30:55.680 --> 00:30:58.580
So we're not trusting in our good works.

481
00:30:58.580 --> 00:31:03.580
We're not trusting in our, like of course we're called to think these things through.

482
00:31:03.580 --> 00:31:05.080
It's put before us here so that we can do that.

483
00:31:05.080 --> 00:31:10.080
But we're not trusting in our intellect or our emotions, how we feel about things.

484
00:31:11.080 --> 00:31:15.080
We're called to put our trust in Jesus.

485
00:31:16.080 --> 00:31:18.080
So what are you putting your trust in?

486
00:31:20.080 --> 00:31:21.080
Hear these words from Jesus.

487
00:31:21.080 --> 00:31:23.080
Probably the most famous words in the Bible.

488
00:31:23.080 --> 00:31:30.080
Found in John chapter 3 and verse 16 that God so loved the world that he gave his only son.

489
00:31:30.080 --> 00:31:38.080
Whoever believes in him, whoever believes in him should not perish but have everlasting life.

490
00:31:39.080 --> 00:31:42.080
So you believe, you live.

491
00:31:43.080 --> 00:31:53.080
And this life that Jesus gives stretches out into eternity, but it's not just about where you go when you die.

492
00:31:53.080 --> 00:31:56.080
Maybe we've thought about the gospel in that way.

493
00:31:56.080 --> 00:31:59.080
It's just about what happens after death.

494
00:31:59.080 --> 00:32:00.080
That's not the case.

495
00:32:00.080 --> 00:32:02.080
Eternal life begins now.

496
00:32:03.080 --> 00:32:07.080
It's about being born of God and living the life that you were made for it now.

497
00:32:07.080 --> 00:32:10.080
And that is the life that only Jesus can give.

498
00:32:11.080 --> 00:32:15.080
And that life with him goes on forever.

499
00:32:16.080 --> 00:32:19.080
And it is the I am, the one who eternally is.

500
00:32:20.080 --> 00:32:23.080
Who is the source of that life.

501
00:32:24.080 --> 00:32:27.080
So the gospel here ends with this call to believe him.

502
00:32:27.080 --> 00:32:31.080
But then in chapter 21, there's a call to his disciples to then follow him.

503
00:32:32.080 --> 00:32:35.080
Where is the life of God, this eternal life seen in our lives.

504
00:32:35.080 --> 00:32:40.080
It's seen as we follow Jesus and learn to be his disciples.

505
00:32:40.080 --> 00:32:41.080
So this is for all of us.

506
00:32:41.080 --> 00:32:50.080
So the call here is to put your faith in the Jesus and by his help live the life that you have been made for as his follower.

507
00:32:50.080 --> 00:32:53.080
And that life is rooted in his name.

508
00:32:54.080 --> 00:33:01.080
One of the wonderful things we see in John is that it doesn't just tell us about Jesus' name.

509
00:33:01.080 --> 00:33:06.080
We have Jesus also calling other people by their name as well.

510
00:33:06.080 --> 00:33:09.080
And he still does that today.

511
00:33:09.080 --> 00:33:13.080
He calls specific people to put their trust in him and to follow him.

512
00:33:13.080 --> 00:33:17.080
I pray that we would all hear him calling us and that we would come.

513
00:33:17.080 --> 00:33:19.080
Let's pray that we might do that.

514
00:33:23.080 --> 00:33:39.080
Thank you for making yourself known to us in Jesus.

515
00:33:39.080 --> 00:33:46.080
Or thank you for making yourself known to us through your word.

516
00:33:47.080 --> 00:33:54.080
And Lord I pray that by your spirit we would each hear not only this name of who you are,

517
00:33:54.080 --> 00:33:58.080
but Lord I pray that we would hear you calling us by name.

518
00:33:58.080 --> 00:34:02.080
And Lord we would put our faith in you.

519
00:34:02.080 --> 00:34:12.080
And Lord I pray that you would help us to follow you and know your life at work in us.

520
00:34:12.080 --> 00:34:21.080
Lord I pray that all of this would lead us to worship you, that we would give you the glory that is due to your name.

521
00:34:21.080 --> 00:34:26.080
We pray all of this in your wonderful name. Amen.

